set_display_header
Disk World creator help
set_display_header

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
set_display_header -  This method allows you to switch the menu header (defaults to "The menu reads:") that appears at the top of the menu on and off.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
void set_display_header(int value)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^value%^RESET%^ - set to 1 to display header or 0 to remove them
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/shops/inherit/pub.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method allows you to switch the menu header (defaults to "The menu
reads:") that appears at the top of the menu on and off.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
query_display_header(), set_menu_header(), query_menu_header()

.EP

